-- Orascom Seeks Compensation for Power Plant Damages, Mal Reports
-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 2012-01-04T07:58:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/orascom-seeks-compensation-for-power-plant-damages-mal-reports.html
Orascom Construction Industries (OCIC)  is
seeking compensation for damages incurred when a power plant it
is building was attacked by village residents and equipment was
set ablaze,  Al Mal  reported, citing Ali Hassan, chairman of the
Cairo Electricity Production Co.  Hassan said initial damage to the North Giza plant was
appraised at 40 million Egyptian pounds ($6.6 million), the
Cairo-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal in Cairo at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  at 
 sev@bloomberg.net . 